SIMPLE: ponderous
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ponderous
<hw>Pon"der*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>ponderosus</ets>, from <ets>pondus</ets>, <ets>-eris</ets>, a
weight: cf. F. <ets>pond⟦eacute⟧reux</ets>. See <er>Ponder</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Very heavy; weighty; <as>as, a <ex>ponderous</ex>
shield; a <ex>ponderous</ex> load; the <ex>ponderous</ex>
elephant.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The sepulcher . . . ⟦br⟧
Hath oped his <qex>ponderous</qex> and marble jaws.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Important; momentous; forcible.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Your
more <xex>ponderous</xex> and settled project.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Heavy; dull; wanting; lightless or spirit; <as>as, a
<ex>ponderous</ex> style; a <ex>ponderous</ex> joke.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Ponderous spar</b></col> <fld>(Min.)</fld>, <cd>heavy
spar, or barytes. See <er>Barite</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ponderously</ent>⟦br⟧
